Rule: Higher education levels like 'Prof-school' or 'Bachelors' are associated with earning more than $50k a year.
Occupations in 'Sales' or Blue-Collar jobs with different conditions can be associated with higher income.
Gender can impact income, with some cases where 'Female' is associated with higher income.
Working more than the standard 40 hours per week can be associated with a higher income.
Race can have an impact on income, with 'Other' being associated with higher income in some cases.
Being 'Self-Employed' can be associated with a higher income compared to being in the 'Private' workclass.
